data.enText: wanting to do sth or wanting sth to happen very much
John was very keen to help.

data.chText: 我们盼着自己学校也参与其中。
data.enText: We are keen that our school should get involved too.

data.chText: 我不太想去参加这次聚会。
data.enText: I wasn't too keen on going to the party.
enthusiastic about an activity or idea, etc.

data.chText: 这个队最热情的支持者之一
data.enText: one of the keenest supporters of the team
liking sb/sth very much; very interested in sb/sth

data.chText: 她不喜欢别人向她发号施令。
data.enText: She's not keen on being told what to do.

data.chText: 思维敏捷的；机灵的；机智的
他对孙子的教育很感兴趣。
data.enText: He took a keen interest in his grandson's education.
Dogs have a keen sense of smell.

data.chText: 我的朋友最会发现便宜货。
data.enText: My friend has a keen eye for (= is good at noticing) a bargain.
involving people competing very hard with each other for sth

data.chText: 要在这所学院就读竞争是非常激烈的。
data.enText: There is keen competition for places at the college.
kept low in order to compete with other prices
having a sharp edge or point
We were keenly aware of the danger.

data.chText: 极其渴望；极为热心；非常热情
data.enText: wanting very much to do well at sth; enthusiastic

before.enText: usually used in the progressive tenses

data.enText: to make a loud high sad sound, when sb has died

ex.chText: 她班上的学生都渴望学习。
ex.enText: All the students in her class are eager to learn.

ex.chText: 我们公司急欲开辟新的市场。
ex.enText: Our company is eager to expand into new markets.

synonyms.bx: 指对即将发生的事情或想要做的事情感到热切和兴奋的，含有迫不及待之意，常后接介词 for 或动词不定式。

ex.chText: 我们急切地等他讲下一段故事。
ex.enText: We waited agog for the next part of his story.

ex.chText: 他们都渴望获知有关世界杯足球赛的消息。
ex.enText: They are all agog to know the news about the World Cup.

synonyms.bx: 指非常激动或迫不及待地想要进一步了解某事的，只作表语。

ex.chText: 他急于改善自己的工作条件。
ex.enText: He is anxious to improve his working conditions.

ex.chText: 管理层亟欲避免另一场罢工。
ex.enText: The management is anxious to avoid another strike.

synonyms.bx: 指非常急切地想做某事或渴望某事发生的。

ex.chText: 这些士兵迫不及待地想要离开伊拉克。
ex.enText: These soldiers are impatient to leave Iraq.
She is impatient for her husband to come back.

synonyms.bx: 指迫切渴望某事发生而不想等待的，只作表语。

ex.enText: She was keen on going to the picnic.

ex.chText: 他们热切盼望春天去欧洲。
ex.enText: They were keen on going to Europe in the spring.
She is keen to pass the exams.

synonyms.bx: 指因兴趣或欲望强烈而急于做某事或渴望某事发生的，通常后接介词 on 或动词不定式。

synonym.guide: 导航词义：热切的，渴望的

tr: a funeral lament sung with loud wailing

example: we lamented the death of the child

tr: having a sharp cutting edge or point
painful as if caused by a sharp instrument

example: had a great time at the party

tr: having or demonstrating ability to recognize or draw fine distinctions
example: an acute observer of politics and politicians
as sharp and incisive as the stroke of a fang

value.def: If you are keen on doing something, you very much want to do it. If you are keen that something should happen, you very much want it to happen.

example.ex: You're not keen on going, are you?...
example.tran: 你不太想去，是吗？

example.ex: Both companies were keen on a merger...
example.tran: 两家公司都很想合并。

example.ex: I'm very keen that the European Union should be as open as possible to trade from Russia...
example.tran: 我热切地希望欧盟尽可能开放与俄罗斯的贸易。

example.ex: She's still keen to keep in touch...
example.tran: 她仍旧很愿意保持联系。

example.ex: I am not keen for her to have a bicycle.
example.tran: 我不太放心她有辆自行车。

gramarinfo.label: v-link ADJ, ADJ <l>on</l> -ing/n, ADJ that, ADJ to-inf

example.ex: ...Doyle's keenness to please.
example.tran: 多伊尔想取悦他人的热切心情

example.ex: ...a keenness for the idea of a co-ordinated approach to development.
example.tran: 想要协调一致搞发展的强烈愿望

value.def: If you are keen on something, you like it a lot and are very enthusiastic about it.

example.ex: I got quite keen on the idea...
example.tran: 我对这个想法燃起了极大的热情。

example.ex: I wasn't too keen on physics and chemistry.
example.tran: 我对物理和化学不是太感喜爱。

example.ex: ...his keenness for the arts.
example.tran: 他对艺术的喜爱

value.def: You use keen to indicate that someone has a lot of enthusiasm for a particular activity and spends a lot of time doing it.

example.ex: She was a keen amateur photographer.
example.tran: 她是业余摄影爱好者。

value.def: If you describe someone as keen, you mean that they have an enthusiastic nature and are interested in everything that they do.

example.ex: He's a very keen student and works very hard...
example.tran: 他是个很好学的学生，学习非常努力。

example.ex: You're all very keen.
example.tran: 你们都很热心。

example.ex: ...the keenness of the students.
example.tran: 学生的好学

value.def: A keen interest or emotion is one that is very intense.

example.ex: He had retained a keen interest in the progress of the work.
example.tran: 他对那项工作的进展一直很关心。

example.ex: ...his keen sense of loyalty.
example.tran: 他强烈的忠诚感

example.ex: She remained keenly interested in international affairs...
example.tran: 她仍旧对国际事务很感兴趣。

example.ex: This is a keenly awaited project.
example.tran: 这是一个让人热切期待的项目。

value.def: If you are a keen supporter of a cause, movement, or idea, you support it enthusiastically.

example.ex: He's been a keen supporter of the Labour Party all his life...
example.tran: 他一生都是工党的热情拥护者。

example.ex: He is a keen advocate of park-and-ride schemes.
example.tran: 他是“停车再换乘”计划的热情拥护者。

value.def: If you say that someone has a keen mind, you mean that they are very clever and aware of what is happening around them.

example.ex: They described him as a man of keen intellect...
example.tran: 他们把他描述成一个才思敏捷的人。

example.ex: Mr Walsh has a keen appreciation of the priorities of the electorate...
example.tran: 沃尔什先生深刻理解选民最为关注的事项。

example.ex: I can see you have a keen sense of humour.
example.tran: 我能看出你极具幽默感。

value.tran: 思维敏捷的；机灵的；机智的

example.ex: They're keenly aware that whatever they decide will set a precedent.
example.tran: 他们深知无论他们的决定是什么，都将开创先例。

value.def: If you have a keen eye or ear, you are able to notice things that are difficult to detect.

example.ex: ...an amateur artist with a keen eye for detail...
example.tran: 对细节非常敏感的业余画家

example.ex: Brand's keen ear caught the trace of an accent.
example.tran: 布兰德敏锐的耳朵听出了口音。

example.ex: Charles listened keenly.
example.tran: 查尔斯竖着耳朵听着。

example.ex: ...his keenly observed portrait.
example.tran: 他栩栩如生的肖像

value.def: If you are keen on someone, you find them sexually attractive and want to get to know them better.

example.ex: Mick has always been very keen on Carla.
example.tran: 米克一直迷恋卡拉。

value.def: A keen fight or competition is one in which the competitors are all trying very hard to win, and it is not easy to predict who will win.

example.ex: There is expected to be a keen fight in the local elections.
example.tran: 预计地方选举的竞争会非常激烈。

example.ex: The contest should be very keenly fought.
example.tran: 比赛将会争夺得非常激烈。

example.ex: The company negotiates very keen prices with their suppliers.
example.tran: 该公司通过讨价还价从供货商那里拿到了很低的价格。

example.ex: The shops also offer a keenly priced curtain-making service.
example.tran: 这些商店也提供价格优惠的窗帘制作服务。

value.def: If someone keens, they cry out or make sounds to express their sorrow at someone's death.

example.ex: He tossed back his head and keened...
example.tran: 他仰天恸哭起来。

example.ex: Someone was making a low, keening noise.
example.tran: 有人正在低声哀泣。

value.def: If you say that someone is mad keen on something, you are emphasizing that they are very enthusiastic about it.

example.ex: So you're not mad keen on science then?...
example.tran: 那么你对科学并不是太感兴趣了？

example.ex: She was mad keen to go.
example.tran: 她非常想去。

example.ex: ...a mad keen golfer.
example.tran: 高尔夫发烧友

value.tran: 对…十分热衷；对…非常热情

trans: 激烈的竞争；竞争激烈；优胜劣汰；激烈竞争
浓厚的兴趣；强烈的兴趣；浓厚兴趣
